## Diff vs. plan + five MUST-HOLD invariants

Matches the approved round-4 plan with no deviations. All five invariants confirmed in the actual diff:

1. Write-then-error: refspec action is appended LAST (init.go:242) and runs inside apply() after the
   write actions; force + remoteChanged + absent returns remoteNotFoundErr only after writes already
   executed. Locked by TestInitExplicitMissingRemoteWritesThenErrors (non-force + force subtests).
2. --force refspec silence: refspecAction force gate returns (nil, nil) for present remote and for all
   cases except explicit-missing-error; dry-run force+present also returns (nil, nil). Locked by the
   strengthened TestInitForceMissingDefaultOriginSucceeds (prefix-specific assertions, not bare summary
   words) and TestInitForceDryRun ("0 to configure", no plan: configure line).
3. --dry-run read-only / never-errors / count-parity: dryRun branch touches only os.Stat / remoteExists;
   dryRun is checked BEFORE the force missing-remote error path, so dry-run never errors on a missing
   remote even under --force. writeScaffoldFile / MkdirAll / WriteFile / git --add are never reached
   under dryRun. Locked by TestInitDryRunWritesNothing, TestInitDryRunMissingRemoteReports,
   TestInitDryRunExistingScaffoldSkips, TestInitDryRunForceMissingRemoteReports.
4. apply() sole print site + byte-identical legacy consts + plan() never calls remoteExists: every
   fmt.Fprintln/Fprintf for action output and the summary lives in apply(); the five legacy strings are
   hoisted to fmt* consts (init.go:32-36) and remain byte-identical; plan() builds the action list and
   never calls remoteExists or returns remoteNotFoundErr (only the refspecAction closure, executed in
   apply, does).
5. configured bucket = statusConfigured + statusAlreadyConfigured; statusNote uncounted: apply tally
   collapses both configured statuses into one counter and has no case for statusNote. Locked by
   TestInitSummaryCounts (re-run reports 2 configured via already-configured).

